{
  "doc_id": "43525",
  "text": "Mice. CD46-IFNAR mice susceptible to MV infection were produced as previously described [CITATION_1] . These mice express hCD46, the human receptor for vaccine MV strains, and lack the IFN-a/b receptor [CITATION_2] . They have been used previously as a model to evaluate the immunogenicity of recombinant MV [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] . Groups of eight week old CD46-IFNAR mice were inoculated intraperitoneally (i.p) with increasing doses of MV1-F4 recombinant virus (10 4 to 10 7 TCID 50 ). Non-immunized mice were used as controls. To assess the early cell-mediated immune responses elicited against both the HIV-1 F4 antigen and the MV vector, mice were euthanized at 7 days post-immunization, spleens were collected and splenocytes purified.",
